newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: Cricket-Queensland lead Tasmania on first innings.
newsitem.headline: Cricket-Queensland lead Tasmania on first innings.

text.p: Queensland pace bowler Andrew Bichel took six for 63 on Thursday to spark a dramatic collapse by the Tasmanian batsmen on the second day of their Sheffield Shield match.
Tasmania took their overnight total of 14 to one to 121 without further loss before Bichel swung into action.
David Boon's side then lost their last nine wickets for 47 and were eventually dismissed for an inadequate 168.
Michael DiVenuto was the best of Tasmania's batsmen, scoring 66 before he fell to swing bowler Adam Dale who took three for 29 in his maiden first-class appearance.
At the close Queensland were 206 for nine in reply with Geoff Foley unbeaten on 62.
Queensland started their innings hesitantly and were 97 for four before Foley came to the crease and steadied the innings.
